Business Brief -- Holderbank Financiere Glaris Ltd.:
   Swiss Firm's Unit Purchases
   Anschutz Corp.'s 6.1% Stake
Anschutz was a minority stockholder in Ideal Basics
Industries, which merged with Dundee Cement Co. to form
Holnam in March 1990. As part of the settlement, Anschutz
Corp. and Phillip F. Anschutz sold their 8.2 million shares
of Holnam stock back to the company at $4.25 a share.
   Holnam, a cement products manufacturing company in Dundee,
Mich., is 95.3% owned by Holderbank Financiere Glaris of
Switzerland.